{
  "stem": "8916.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's so-- it's so traditional.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We learned [INAUDIBLE] on mandolin and [INAUDIBLE], which was for us a-- the place where we were, really.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, we were doing the same-- the things that we were singing about.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in Narewka, along the-- Narewka-- the city of Narewka, there is a river.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And for us, this was a-- a place to be.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We-- in the summertime, we go-- we went swimming there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the wintertime, we skated on it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was just-- there was a meadow between our-- the buildings or the homes and-- and the river, and as children, I recall as a very pleasant time to have-- to be able to just run out there and go swimming.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In the summertime, we mostly ran around barefoot, you know, really free souls.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as I said earlier, we had our grandparents on either side of the street, and we had friends and uncles and aunts and-- who lived almost across the street from us.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you know, the-- during my period of time, the-- my memory, the relationship between the Jews and the non-Jews was very congenial in that there was sort of a symbiotic relationship in that there was an exchange in commerce and exchange in goods and production, for example.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had neighbors who were non-Jewish neighbors and as children we played together.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, anti-Semitism in Poland, especially in eastern Poland, was a way of life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It-- I-- it was so strong and it was so common that we just accepted it, and we-- we just worked around it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, for example, we had this woman who lived almost across the street from us, and she used to chase around because she didn't want us to cross-- to walk in front of her house.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
